<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Connecting_the_Knobster">Connecting the Knobster</span></h2>
<p>The Knobster uses a USB C connection. It can be connected to either USB 2.0 or USB 3.x. There is no need for installing additional drivers.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Verifying_the_Knobster_is_connected">Verifying the Knobster is connected</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/7/74/Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg/200px-Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg" decoding="async" width="200" height="110" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/7/74/Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg/300px-Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/74/Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg/400px-Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_air_manager_4_0.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Knobster connected to Air Manager</div></div></div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Air_Manager">Air Manager</span></h3>
<p>With the Knobster plugged in to USB, go to the Air Manager Home tab and verify that it is connected.
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/c/ce/Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg/200px-Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg" decoding="async" width="200" height="110" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/c/ce/Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg/300px-Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/ce/Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg/400px-Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_air_player_4_0.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Knobster connected to Air Player</div></div></div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Air_Player">Air Player</span></h3>
<p>Plugin the Knobster before starting Air Player. In the Air Manager Home tab, select Air Player and press the drop down arrow. You will see the Knobster listed together with all your panels.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Enabling_the_Knobster_for_panels">Enabling the Knobster for panels</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/3/3f/Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg/200px-Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg" decoding="async" width="200" height="110" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/3/3f/Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg/300px-Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3f/Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg/400px-Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Knobster_select_air_manager_4_0.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Knobster selected for a certain panel in Air Manager</div></div></div>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Air_Manager_2">Air Manager</span></h3>
<p>Go to the Home tab and selected the panel that should be used with the Knobster. Scroll down in the panel settings and find the Knobster settings. Select your Knobster from the drop down box.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Air_Player_2">Air Player</span></h3>
<p>Go to the Home tab in Air Manager, click the drop down button next to Air Player and selected the panel that should be used with the Knobster. Scroll down in the panel settings and find the Knobster settings. Select your Knobster from the drop down box.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Using_the_Knobster">Using the Knobster</span></h2>
<p>On your Knobster enabled panel select either a dial or switch with your touch screen or mouse, a yellow circle will highlight the selected dial or switch. Now turn the Knobster knob(s) to actuate the software dial or switch.
Some dials and switches have a button incorporated, press the Knobster inner knob to actuate the software button.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Single_dial">Single dial</span></h3>
<p>With a single dial selected, either in the inner or outer knob can be used to actuate the dial.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Double_dial">Double dial</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Doubledialselected.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/c/c3/Doubledialselected.jpg/200px-Doubledialselected.jpg" decoding="async" width="200" height="64" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/c/c3/Doubledialselected.jpg/300px-Doubledialselected.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c3/Doubledialselected.jpg/400px-Doubledialselected.jpg 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Doubledialselected.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Example of a Double/dual dial selected</div></div></div>
<p>With a double/dual dial selected, the (big) outer knob operates the bottom dial, the (small) inner knob operates the top dial. This is for example used with COM / NAV radios.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Switch">Switch</span></h3>
<p>Switches with three or more positions can be operated with either knob.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Buttons">Buttons</span></h3>
<p>Only buttons that are incorporated into a dial or switch can be operated by pressing the inner knob (Push button).
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Frequently_Asked_Questions">Frequently Asked Questions</span></h2>
<h3><span id="I.27m_using_Microsoft_Windows_7_and_my_Knobster_is_not_recognized"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="I&#39;m_using_Microsoft_Windows_7_and_my_Knobster_is_not_recognized">I'm using Microsoft Windows 7 and my Knobster is not recognized</span></h3>
<p>Older versions of Windows 7 are missing necessary USB drivers. You can download these <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://siminnovations.com/wiki/files/WinUsb_Device.cab">here</a>.
</p>
